-- Australia shares close modestly lower, most sectors down
-- 
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 02:15AM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, June 24 (Reuters) - Australian shares slipped 0.4 percent on Tuesday, following Wall Street lower as investors sold local equities across the board, outweighing a jump in department store operator David Jones Ltd <DJS.AX>, a takeover target.[ID:nL4N0P509G]

